title: Cape Hockey runs record to 9-0 with 6-0 Shutout Win Over Sussex Tech
text: Cape Hockey runs record to 9-0 with 6-0 Shutout Win Over Sussex Tech Oct 13, 2015 Photo by: Dan Cook Cape's Tess Bernheimer makes a backhand pass into the scoring circle as Sussex Tech junior Jazmyne Marino plays defense. The Cape field hockey team shutout Sussex Tech at Champions Stadium Tuesday night ,October 13, scoring 3 goals in each period for a 6 to 0 victory. Cape goals were scored by Sydney Ostroski 2, Tess Bernheimer 2 with single goals from Katie Klabe and Katie Frederick. Goalies Riley Shields and Lori Ferguson shared the shutout. The Vikings improved to 9-0 on the season. The ravens drop to 3-4-2. Cape hosts Sussex Central on Thursday, October 22, at 6 p.m for Senior Night. Look for further details in the , October 16, Friday Edition of the Cape Gazette. Cape's Sydney Ostroski, left, celebrates her goal with defender Lizzie Frederick. (Photo by: Dan Cook) Senior midfielder Erin Coverdale controls the ball. (Photo by: Dan Cook) Cape freshman Alia Marshall moves the ball into the scoring circle. (Photo by: Dan Cook)
